text:
Sup everyone, ahead of our voting meeting tomorrow here is what our client had to say about our project proposals:

```
Hey Jack,

Thanks for putting the proposal together and getting that over to us, really appreciate the effort. We're liking two of the concepts, and have a few questions/concerns on both -

WiFi Viz - Cool idea, but we're a little concerned about how it's going to come into fruition. Would have been nice to see more of the executional plan and details.

Mood Ring 2.0 - This is probably our top contender, but it's got to scale and be able to continuously scale pretty easy. Actually that continuously scaling idea is one we're excited about.

I've forwarded the proposal on to our stakeholder James and will follow up when we hear her weigh in. Hope you have a great weekend.
```

also I've set up another meeting on Wednesday where we're going to start digging into the nitty gritty of the project we choose tomorrow. I hope to come out of that with a game plan we can run with, at least for the next couple of weeks. Everything from materials we'll need to how we're going to organize the team. It'd be great to dig into actually making our product as soon as we can!

Alright guys, scratch the voting part because our client has officially decided to move forward with the Mood Ring project! Let's keep tomorrow's meeting and instead use it to start fleshing out the operations side of our project - scheduling, materials, structure, the works. Bring your fre$h ideas on scalability and execution with you!
